Compare Models

Compare metrics for multiple models side by side to see how they stack up against each other. For example, comparing segments in your data can reveal the most important variables in each segment.

To compare models:

In Model Metrics, click Compare to another model.
Select two or three models to compare.
Click Show Comparison.
Einstein Discovery compares the selected models, and then opens a new tab showing an overview of the results.

Model Name	Name of the model.
Dataset	Name of the dataset associated with the model.
Model Type	Type of model. Example: RegressionGLM
Created Date	Model version date.

To view comparative metrics, click the Metrics tab.
To view the top correlations in the data, click the Data tab.
title: Comparing Machine Learning Models
